Name: bladder adenocarcinoma
Definition: A bladder carcinoma that derives_from epithelial cells of glandular origin.

Name: bladder squamous cell carcinoma
Definition: A carcinoma of bladder that is manifested in squamous cells of the bladder.

Name: bladder urothelial carcinoma
Definition: A bladder carcinoma that has_material_basis_in transitional cells located_in the lining of the bladder.

Name: bladder urachal carcinoma
Definition: An anxiety disorder that is characterized by unexpected and repeated episodes of intense fear accompanied by physical symptoms that may include chest pain

Name: obsolete schistosoma hematobium-related bladder squamous cell carcinoma
Definition: An anxiety disorder that is characterized by unexpected and repeated episodes of intense fear accompanied by physical symptoms that may include chest pain

Name: urinary bladder small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma
Definition: A hematologic cancer that is located in the blood or bone marrow that doesn't respond to treatment.
Synonym: small cell/neuroendocrine carcinoma of urinary bladder

Name: Jewett-Marshall bladder cancer
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the kidneys

Name: obsolete inherited neuropathy
Definition: An organ system benign neoplasm that is located_in the kidneys

Name: superficial urinary bladder cancer
Definition: A carcinoma of bladder that originates in the epithelial cells (the internal lining) of the bladder wall and is limited to this area.
